when you have crappy advance sales.

97
00:05:20.250 --> 00:05:21.875
This is gonna close us.

98
00:05:22.625 --> 00:05:25.041
What didn't they like? Was it the hip-hop?

99
00:05:25.125 --> 00:05:27.083
Yes. but not only that.

100
00:05:27.166 --> 00:05:30.833
-For God's sake. Sheldon. Just read it.
-What? Read.

101
00:05:30.916 --> 00:05:33.250
[Sheldon] Okay. just the highlights.

102
00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:37.208
"Barry Glickman's FDR might just be
the most insultingly misguided.

103
00:05:37.291 --> 00:05:39.500
offensive. and laughable performance

104
00:05:39.583 --> 00:05:44.000
that this reviewer has ever had
the squirming misfortune to endure."

105
00:05:46.750 --> 00:05:48.208
That's not so bad.

106
00:05:48.833 --> 00:05:51.166
-Do her. Do her.
-I'm just saying.

107
00:05:51.250 --> 00:05:52.083
Oh? Mmm.

108
00:05:52.166 --> 00:05:54.416
"Watching Dee Dee Allen's
Eleanor Roosevelt

109
00:05:54.500 --> 00:05:57.208
croaking out a heavy-handed
message of activism

110
00:05:57.291 --> 00:05:59.708
is like paying an aging drag queen

111
00:05:59.791 --> 00:06:03.041
to shove a syrup-soaked
American flag down my throat."

112
00:06:03.625 --> 00:06:05.208
Well. that…

113
00:06:05.291 --> 00:06:07.916
That's not criticism.

114
00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.250
That's just… It's just a per…
[voice breaking] …a personal attack.

115
00:06:12.333 --> 00:06:16.833
"If you're considering buying a ticket
to this show. do yourself a favor."

116
00:06:16.916 --> 00:06:19.791
"Buy a few feet
of good. heavy rope instead

117
00:06:19.875 --> 00:06:21.666
and then go hang yourself."

118
00:06:21.750 --> 00:06:25.541
[Barry] Oh. God! Oh. God!

119
00:06:26.666 --> 00:06:29.416
[mutters] What?
Was the show really that bad?

120
00:06:29.500 --> 00:06:32.333
It's not the show. It's you two.

121
00:06:32.416 --> 00:06:34.208
You're just not likeable.

122
00:06:34.916 --> 00:06:35.916
-What?
-What?

123
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.291
Nobody likes a narcissist.

124
00:06:39.208 --> 00:06:40.708
-Oh. this… [clears throat]
-Oh. that.

125
00:06:40.791 --> 00:06:44.291
Leave it to me. I'll go and try
and change the narrative once again.

126
00:06:44.375 --> 00:06:48.791
-I hate this world! This is bullshit!
-Just horrible. It's just… It hurts.

127
00:06:48.875 --> 00:06:52.000
It… It hurts my heart.

128
00:06:52.083 --> 00:06:54.375
-[Barry exhales]
-Where did everybody go?

129
00:06:55.333 --> 00:06:58.583
-What can I get you?
-[both] Yola Mezcal blackberry smash.

130
00:06:59.166 --> 00:07:01.250
[bartender] My condolences. Dee Dee.

131
00:07:01.333 --> 00:07:03.791
But remember. you have friends.

132
00:07:03.875 --> 00:07:06.458
Thank you. Who are you?

133
00:07:07.500 --> 00:07:08.583
Trent Oliver.

134
00:07:09.291 --> 00:07:10.541
Uh. oh…

135
00:07:11.041 --> 00:07:14.125
-We've done five shows together.
-Oh. really? Oh. my God.

136
00:07:14.208 --> 00:07:16.375
Trent went to Juilliard.
Won't shut up about it.

137
00:07:16.458 --> 00:07:19.583
-Oh. right. Trent! Of course. Trent!
-Trent.

138
00:07:19.666 --> 00:07:20.791
[Trent and Dee Dee chuckle]

139
00:07:22.166 --> 00:07:23.541
Why are you dressed like a waiter?

140
00:07:24.583 --> 00:07:26.916
-I'm in between gigs at the moment.
-[Dee Dee] Hmm.

141
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:31.500
Honestly. Dee Dee. I feel adrift
as I did in my days before Juilliard.

142
00:07:31.583 --> 00:07:32.666
Oh. my God.

143
00:07:32.750 --> 00:07:35.875
You see. my passions are fueled
by the power of Lady Theater

144
00:07:35.958 --> 00:07:39.000
and how she can.
with a gentle touch of her hand.

145
00:07:39.083 --> 00:07:41.083
sculpt a human soul.

146
00:07:41.166 --> 00:07:43.833
-But we learned at Juilliard…
-Oh. mother of God.

147
00:07:43.916 --> 00:07:47.791
If I could soliloquize.
"If you prick me. do I not bleed?"

148
00:07:49.666 --> 00:07:52.541
"And if you do not pay me.
do I not still act?"

149
00:07:52.625 --> 00:07:54.208
That might be enough.

150
00:07:54.291 --> 00:07:56.000
Still. I have played Hamlet.

151
00:07:56.083 --> 00:08:01.875
and yet I'm only known as that guy
from the beloved early aughts' sitcom…

152
00:08:02.458 --> 00:08:03.708
[Trent] Talk to the Hand.

153
00:08:03.791 --> 00:08:05.041
["Hold My Hand" playing]

154
00:08:05.125 --> 00:08:06.541
[audience laughing]

155
00:08:07.875 --> 00:08:10.791
I question
the very meaning of my existence.

156
00:08:10.875 --> 00:08:12.916
[jazzy tune playing]

157
00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:17.125
Maggie Smith once approached me
in a men's bathroom and she said.

158
00:08:17.208 --> 00:08:19.791
"Who sent you? Was it Michelle Dockery?"

159
00:08:19.875 --> 00:08:23.708
"Because the court said 500 yards."
You could tell she was scared.

160
00:08:23.791 --> 00:08:26.958
-Hey. guys!
-[Barry] Angie! Angie.

161
00:08:27.041 --> 00:08:30.291
I'm sorry your show
closed on opening night again!

162
00:08:30.375 --> 00:08:31.916
[Barry and Dee Dee groan]

163
00:08:32.416 --> 00:08:35.083
Welcome to the world
of the unemployed. Top me off.

164
00:08:35.166 --> 00:08:36.750
I thought you were in Chicago.

165
00:08:36.833 --> 00:08:39.583
[groans] I just quit.

166
00:08:40.208 --> 00:08:43.708
Twenty years in the chorus and they still
wouldn't let me play Roxie Hart.

167
00:08:43.791 --> 00:08:45.958
-[Dee Dee] Aw.
-You wanna know who's playing the role?

168
00:08:46.041 --> 00:08:47.416
-Kelly Ripa?
-Cher?

169
00:08:47.500 --> 00:08:49.166
-Connie Chung.
-Kris Jenner?

170
00:08:49.250 --> 00:08:50.833
No. Tina Louise.

171
00:08:51.750 --> 00:08:53.916
Ginger from Gilligan's Island.

172
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:55.625
Oh. my God. is she still alive?

173
00:08:56.708 --> 00:08:58.666
[laughs]

174
00:09:04.416 --> 00:09:05.625
[sighs]

175
00:09:09.916 --> 00:09:12.250
We're wasting our lives.

176
00:09:12.333 --> 00:09:16.250
Hmm. it's true.
At least we're all in the same boat.

177
00:09:16.333 --> 00:09:20.416
"Misery acquaints a man
with strange bedfellows."

178
00:09:20.500 --> 00:09:22.583
-[Barry] Oh. my God.
-That's from The Tempest.

179
00:09:22.666 --> 00:09:26.541
Okay. one. shut up.
Two. I refuse to give up. okay?

180
00:09:26.625 --> 00:09:30.458
We're… We're still celebrities.
We still have power.

181
00:09:30.541 --> 00:09:31.666
[chuckles]

182
00:09:31.750 --> 00:09:34.166
Now. The Times
sort of castrated you as it were.

183
00:09:34.250 --> 00:09:35.083
[Barry sighs]

184
00:09:35.166 --> 00:09:38.416
Yep. They wrote you off
as aging narcissists.

185
00:09:38.500 --> 00:09:41.375
I still don't understand
what's wrong with that.

186
00:09:41.458 --> 00:09:45.625
There's a very simple way
that we can still love ourselves

187
00:09:45.708 --> 00:09:50.500
yet appear to be
decent human beings. okay?

188
00:09:50.583 --> 00:09:53.166
We will become celebrity activists.

189
00:09:53.250 --> 00:09:55.500
-[Angie] Oh! Brilliant!
-[Barry] Right?

190
00:09:55.583 --> 00:09:57.875
-All we need is a cause.
-A cause célèbre.

191
00:09:57.958 --> 00:10:00.375
Everybody think of some causes. Go.

192
00:10:00.458 --> 00:10:02.416
-Um. poverty?
-Too big.

193
00:10:02.500 --> 00:10:03.750
World hunger.

194
00:10:03.833 --> 00:10:07.625
That is also a major thing.
No. we need something we can handle.

195
00:10:07.708 --> 00:10:11.166
Some little injustice
we can drive to. Recycling.

196
00:10:11.250 --> 00:10:13.541
-Let's see what's trending.
-[Barry] Recycling's good.

197
00:10:13.625 --> 00:10:16.833
-Why are there so many award shows?
-Parking.

198
00:10:16.916 --> 00:10:20.000
-[Barry] Or the TVs in the back of cabs.
-Oh! Oh. yeah. what about this girl?

199
00:10:20.875 --> 00:10:22.750
Oh. my gosh. Check this out.

200
00:10:22.833 --> 00:10:24.541
-[Barry] What girl?
-It's all over Twitter.

201
00:10:24.625 --> 00:10:25.458
[Barry] Oh.

202
00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:28.166
She's from Edgewater. Indiana.

203
00:10:29.166 --> 00:10:33.291
She's a lesbian. She wanted to take
her girlfriend to the high school prom.

204
00:10:33.375 --> 00:10:35.958
and the PTA went apeshit
and they canceled it.

205
00:10:36.041 --> 00:10:38.000
They canceled prom?

206
00:10:38.083 --> 00:10:40.125
-Are they allowed to do that?
-No.

207
00:10:40.208 --> 00:10:42.125
[reporter] Principal Hawkins.
your response.

208
00:10:42.208 --> 00:10:45.000
The first thing I'm going to do
is contact the Indiana state's attorney.

209
00:10:45.083 --> 00:10:48.416
This is not about school rules.
This is a civil rights case.

210
00:10:48.500 --> 00:10:49.583
Wait. seriously?

211
00:10:49.666 --> 00:10:53.458
I'm betting pressure from the state's
attorney will stop these bigots cold.

212
00:10:53.541 --> 00:10:55.541
It better.
Because I'll tell you this much.

213
00:10:55.625 --> 00:10:58.000
If word gets out.
people are gonna get mad.

214
00:10:58.083 --> 00:10:59.375
This pisses me off.

215
00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:02.500
The next thing you know.
some modern-day Eleanor Roosevelt

216
00:11:02.583 --> 00:11:05.375
is gonna march down here
and all hell's gonna break loose.

217
00:11:06.833 --> 00:11:09.791
We have got to go down there
and raise holy hell.

218
00:11:09.875 --> 00:11:12.333
We will be the biggest thing
to happen in Indiana

219
00:11:12.416 --> 00:11:14.625
since… whatever's happened in Indiana.

220
00:11:14.708 --> 00:11:17.708
-So this is it? This is our cause?
-Yes. Are you with me?

221
00:11:17.791 --> 00:11:19.541
[all cheer]

222
00:11:19.625 --> 00:11:21.166
-We'll have a rally!
-Yes!

223
00:11:21.250 --> 00:11:24.375
-We'll have picket signs!
-We'll make T-shirts.

224
00:11:24.458 --> 00:11:26.666
We'll get Sheldon to tag along.
He can find us a venue.

225
00:11:26.750 --> 00:11:28.208
Oh. wow!

226
00:11:28.291 --> 00:11:32.125
-Can we actually do this?
-You bet your sweet MILF ass we can!

227
00:11:32.208 --> 00:11:33.500
[all laughing]

228
00:11:33.583 --> 00:11:34.666
[exhales]

229
00:11:36.541 --> 00:11:38.000
We are gonna prove…

230
00:11:38.666 --> 00:11:40.875
♪ That in this day and age ♪

231
00:11:40.958 --> 00:11:45.166
♪ Being gay isn't a crime ♪

232
00:11:45.875 --> 00:11:52.583
♪ This is our moment to change the world ♪

233
00:11:53.333 --> 00:11:56.125
-♪ One lesbian… ♪
-[Trent] ♪ Lesbian ♪

234
00:11:56.208 --> 00:11:59.000
-[Dee Dee] ♪ Lesbian ♪
-[Angie] ♪ Lesbian ♪

235
00:11:59.916 --> 00:12:03.000
♪ At a time! ♪

236
00:12:05.583 --> 00:12:08.708
♪ We're gonna help that little lesbian ♪

237
00:12:08.791 --> 00:12:10.916
♪ Whether she likes it or not ♪

238
00:12:12.208 --> 00:12:14.708
♪ When you're a legendary thespian ♪

239
00:12:14.791 --> 00:12:16.416
♪ First. you help the distressed ♪

240
00:12:16.500 --> 00:12:18.125
♪ Then you help the distraught ♪

241
00:12:18.833 --> 00:12:21.958
